{"article_id":"gsQXfJWt0TvTSBCj","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"( CNN )","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"The House impeachment managers and President Donald Trump 's legal team took their final shots Monday","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"to pitch to any senators","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"still on the fence in the President 's impeachment trial ,","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"even if the outcome is a foregone conclusion .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"The impeachment managers and defense counsel made their closing arguments , ahead of the final vote on Wednesday at 4 p.m . ET .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"The Senate is poised to acquit Trump ,","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"as a conviction would require a two-thirds majority ,","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"but there still is some uncertainty over the margin of the vote","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"- and whether any senators cross party lines .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"One of the possible fence-crossers , Republican Sen. Lisa Murkowski of Alaska , said on the Senate floor Monday evening","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"that she would vote to acquit the President","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"The endgame of the trial is set this week","depth":4},{"id":13,"text":"after the Senate voted last week to defeat a motion","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"for subpoenaing witnesses and documents ,","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"which would have extended the proceedings .","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"In that vote ,","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"which failed 49-51 ,","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"two Republicans , Sens . Mitt Romney of Utah and Susan Collins of Maine , joined with Democrats .","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"In his closing arguments , House Intelligence Chairman Adam Schiff acknowledged","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"that the votes would n't be there","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"to remove the President from office .","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"But the California Democrat focused on the Senate Republicans","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"who believe the core of the House 's case","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"- that the President withheld a White House meeting and $ 400 million in security aid","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"to pressure Ukraine to investigate former Vice President Joe Biden -","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"charging","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"they must vote to remove the President .","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"`` If you find","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"that the House has proved ( its ) case","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"and still vote to acquit ,","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"you 'll name will be tied to his with a cord of steel and through all of history , ''","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"Schiff said ,","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"warning","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"`` history will not be kind to Donald Trump . '' `` But if you find the courage","depth":14},{"id":35,"text":"to stand up to him ,","depth":15},{"id":36,"text":"to speak the awful truth to his rank falsehood ,","depth":15},{"id":37,"text":"your place will be among the Davids","depth":14},{"id":38,"text":"who took on Goliath ,","depth":14},{"id":39,"text":"if only you will say enough , ''","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"he added .","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"`` Is there one among you","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"who will say enough ? ' ''","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"The House impeachment managers detailed their case","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"but also harkened back to history ,","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"citing Founding Father Alexander Hamilton , President Abraham Lincoln and poet and novelist Maya Angelou .","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"Rep. Jason Crow , a freshman Colorado Democrat , pointed to a quote from the `` Harry Potter '' character Albus Dumbledore","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"he said","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"hung in his son 's bedroom :","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"`` It is our choices that show who we truly are , far more than our abilities . ''","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"The President 's team argued","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"that House Democrats have been insistent on impeaching Trump","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"since the President was inaugurated in January 2017 .","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"The President 's personal attorney Jay Sekulow played a video montage","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"- backed by a soundtrack out of a campaign ad -","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"of House lawmakers","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"they supported impeachment over the past three years .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"`` These types of impeachments must end , ''","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"said White House counsel Pat Cipollone .","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"`` You will vindicate the right","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"to vote ,","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"you will vindicate the Constitution ,","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"you will vindicate the rule of law","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"by rejecting these articles .","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"And I ask you to do that on a bipartisan basis this week","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"and end the era of impeachment , once and for all . ''","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"After the arguments wrapped up ,","depth":6},{"id":69,"text":"senators had two days","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"to go to the floor","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"and explain their votes .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"A handful of senators in both parties have still not said","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"whether they will vote to convict or acquit the President on the two articles of impeachment","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"- abuse of power and obstruct of Congress -","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"that the House passed in December .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"On the Republican side , Collins , Romney and Murkowski are being eyed by Democrats as possible crossovers .","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"Murkowski announced Monday","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"that she would not vote to acquit the President , however ,","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"which was not a big surprise","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"given she also voted against calling witnesses .","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"In the final floor speech of the day , Murkowski criticized all sides","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"-- the House , the Senate and the President --","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"for the process","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"that 's culminated in the Senate 's impeachment vote this week .","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"But she concluded","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"she could not vote to remove the President from office .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"`` I can not vote to convict .","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"The Constitution provides for impeachment","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"but does not demand it in all instances , ''","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"Murkowski said .","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"`` The President 's name is on ballots","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"that have already been cast .","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"The voters will pronounce a verdict in nine months .","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"And we must trust their judgment . ''","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"Murkowski 's argument was similar to that of Republican Sen. Lamar Alexander of Tennessee ,","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"who was a pivotal vote last week","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"on whether to call witnesses .","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"Alexander said","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"the House had proved its case --","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"but that the conduct was not impeachable .","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"`` The President 's behavior was shameful and wrong , ''","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"Murkowski said Monday .","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"`` The House failed in its responsibilities ,","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"and the Senate , the Senate , should be ashamed by the rank partisanship","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"that has been on display here ...","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"It is clear to me that few in this chamber approached this with a genuinely open mind . ''","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"Among Democrats , Sens . Joe Manchin of West Virginia , Doug Jones of Alabama and Kyrsten Sinema of Arizona are seen as possible crossovers .","depth":5},{"id":108,"text":"Manchin took to the floor Monday afternoon","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"to explain his thinking , but not his vote .","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"`` I remain undecided on how I will vote , ''","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"Manchin said ,","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"explaining","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"that the vote has `` weighed heavily on me . ''","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"Manchin praised the case","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"that the House had made against the President ,","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"but also bemoaned the partisan nature of the impeachment","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"that failed to get any Republican support in the House .","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"He proposed","depth":14},{"id":119,"text":"a censure of the President would be a more effective option","depth":15},{"id":120,"text":"- and one","depth":16},{"id":121,"text":"that could garner a bipartisan majority .","depth":16},{"id":122,"text":"Senators in both parties on Monday dismissed censure as an alternative ,","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"and Manchin acknowledged","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"he would ultimately have to decide how he will vote","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"to remove Trump from office .","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"`` I am truly struggling with this decision","depth":14},{"id":127,"text":"and will come to a conclusion reluctantly , ''","depth":14},{"id":128,"text":"he said .","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"Jones said","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"he was going to be listening to the closing arguments","depth":13},{"id":131,"text":"as he decided what to do .","depth":13},{"id":132,"text":"`` I 'm getting there , ''","depth":14},{"id":133,"text":"he told reporters Monday","depth":14},{"id":134,"text":"when asked","depth":14},{"id":135,"text":"if he knew","depth":15},{"id":136,"text":"how he would vote .","depth":15},{"id":137,"text":"`` I 'm going through all my notes .","depth":14},{"id":138,"text":"I 'm going through everything ,","depth":14},{"id":139,"text":"and I really do want to hear the arguments and some conversations from colleagues . ''","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"Inside the Senate chamber on Monday , things were more subdued than the previous week ,","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"with fewer senators taking notes","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"and more eyes wandering around the room .","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"During Monday 's lunch break in between presentations , the undeclared senators came together on the Senate floor .","depth":8},{"id":144,"text":"Sinema chatted with Sen. John Thune , a South Dakota Republican and the Senate majority whip .","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"The two eventually joined in a conversation with Collins and Murkowski .","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"It 's unknown if they were just making small talk","depth":14},{"id":147,"text":"or talking about the final vote","depth":14},{"id":148,"text":"-","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"at one point , Murkowski could be heard from the press gallery above the chamber","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"making a comment about the Super Bowl .","depth":13},{"id":151,"text":"At the tail end of the lunch break , Manchin and Murkowski whispered back and forth at Manchin 's desk .","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"When the Senate trial ended for the day ,","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"Manchin spoke to Schiff for several minutes .","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"After Monday 's closing arguments , senators began making speeches","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"to explain their votes publicly on the Senate floor , a welcome chance for many senators","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"who have been barred from speaking in the Senate for the duration of the trial .","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"Senators will be able to speak between now and Wednesday 's final vote .","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"The setup was the result of frantic negotiations on Friday","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"for mapping out the final stages of the impeachment trial .","depth":10},{"id":160,"text":"Many Republicans ,","depth":13},{"id":161,"text":"particularly those","depth":14},{"id":162,"text":"allied with Trump ,","depth":14},{"id":163,"text":"wanted to push to end the trial after Friday 's witness vote ,","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"even if it pushed the final verdict into the middle of the night Saturday .","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"But several Republicans ,","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"including Collins and Murkowski ,","depth":13},{"id":167,"text":"wanted the chance","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"to speak","depth":12},{"id":169,"text":"to explain their votes .","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"During the 1999 Bill Clinton impeachment trial , the Senate spent three days in closed session","depth":11},{"id":171,"text":"to deliberate .","depth":11},{"id":172,"text":"Democrats , meanwhile , had 2020 considerations","depth":14},{"id":173,"text":"- with Sens . Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts , Bernie Sanders of Vermont and Amy Klobuchar of Minnesota","depth":14},{"id":174,"text":"eager to spend the weekend in Iowa .","depth":13},{"id":175,"text":"Plus , they were n't interested in allowing the President to be acquitted ahead of Tuesday 's State of the Union address .","depth":12},{"id":176,"text":"So the two sides agreed to hold closing arguments on Monday ,","depth":12},{"id":177,"text":"which the 2020 candidates returned to Washington for","depth":13},{"id":178,"text":"before darting back to Iowa for the caucuses Wednesday evening .","depth":13},{"id":179,"text":"The trial is wrapping up","depth":9},{"id":180,"text":"without hearing from former national security adviser John Bolton ,","depth":10},{"id":181,"text":"who became a key focal point of the witnesses debate","depth":11},{"id":182,"text":"after allegations emerged in his draft book manuscript","depth":12},{"id":183,"text":"that Trump told him","depth":13},{"id":184,"text":"the aid to Ukraine was conditioned on the investigations .","depth":13},{"id":185,"text":"But the House could still pursue Bolton afterward .","depth":11},{"id":186,"text":"Schiff sought Bolton 's testimony in the House impeachment inquiry last year ,","depth":12},{"id":187,"text":"though he did not pursue a subpoena","depth":13},{"id":188,"text":"after Bolton 's lawyer threatened to take it to court .","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"Schiff was coy on Sunday","depth":11},{"id":190,"text":"about whether he will pursue Bolton again .","depth":11},{"id":191,"text":"`` I do n't want to comment to this point on what our plans may or may not be with respect to John Bolton ,","depth":10},{"id":192,"text":"but I will say this :","depth":13},{"id":193,"text":"whether it 's before -- in testimony before the House --","depth":15},{"id":194,"text":"or it 's in his book","depth":16},{"id":195,"text":"or it 's in one form or another ,","depth":16},{"id":196,"text":"the truth will come out ,","depth":15},{"id":197,"text":"will continue to come out , ''","depth":15},{"id":198,"text":"Schiff said on CBS","depth":12},{"id":199,"text":"' `` Face the Nation . ''","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":399,"left":0,"right":398,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":398,"left":217,"right":397,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":217,"left":210,"right":216,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":210,"left":204,"right":209,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":204,"left":203,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":203,"left":202,"right":4,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":202,"left":1,"right":201,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":201,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":2